  "texts": [
    "[11]- [13].The system complexity and uncertainty at the operational level have significantly increased due to highly flexible loads (EVs) and integration of distributed renewable energy resources (DERs).",
    "[3], [14], [15], making traditional modelbased control approaches ineffective [4], [16].",
    "Particularly, such centralized architectures often face impediments due to latency, single-point failures, and scalability, reducing their effectiveness for the decentralized structure of the modern smart grids [5], [17].",
    "Therefore, adaptable control architectures with standardized interfaces are warranted.",
    "They help resolve the core issue of effective coordination between spatio-temporally dispersed components, since these components may operate under different control regimes."
